          "notes": "This module excels at narrative framing (Stanford Smallville, Air Canada case, AutoGPT origin story) and concept accuracy, with rigorous sourcing and clear distinctions between marketing hype and formal definitions. However, it critically fails on D5 (Applied Outcome): the three labs are conversational AI dialogue sandboxes with no executable code, verifiable outputs, or clear success criteria, making it impossible for learners to demonstrate mastery. Lesson 4 content is also vague filler that undermines momentum. The module reads as strong theory education but delivers weak hands-on capability building.",
          "topIssue": "D5 Labs are unexecutable and unmeasurable. Replace conversational AI sandboxes with actual classification tasks (given 5 real products, classify tool/assistant/agent with explanations), diagnostic worksheets (given failure scenario, map to component + propose fix with validation), and autonomy-level design documents (specify reversibility/blast-radius for a use case, justify autonomy level choice, peer-review or system-grade). Current labs leave learners unable to prove they can apply the frameworks independently.",
